                  <persName id="t18290409-99-person1008">
                  JOSEPH 
                  JOWERS
               <interp inst="t18290409-99-person1008" type="surname" value="JOWERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-99-person1008" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-99-person1008" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Sarah Ashbridge - she is <rs id="t18290409-99-viclabel578" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-99-victim1007 t18290409-99-viclabel578"></join>. At five o'clock in the afternoon, of the 3d of April, I saw the prisoner and three more pulling about a pair of trousers inside her shop; they all went away three times and came back again, and each time they took out some pins - when they had taken them all out, the prisoner and another came back; the prisoner took them down, folded them up, and had gone about half a yard from the door - I missed them, went out and took him with them in his hand; he begged my pardon, and said he would not do so any more.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-99-person1009">
                  JOSEPH 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18290409-99-person1009" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
